## ⚠️ Human review required before publish — read first

**Oliver Tree died on 2026-06-14** (aged 32) in the Rio de Janeiro mid-air helicopter collision. I verified this is real, not a hoax (Wikipedia's dedicated crash article, NBC/BBC/Guardian/Variety, a Snopes debunk of the "faked death" theory, father Jesse Nickell's confirmation). This draft is therefore a **posthumous legacy profile written ~3 weeks after his death** (memorial 2026-07-25). I wrote the death soberly and reserved it for the final section; the typing is about how he lived, and the tragedy deepens the thesis without becoming a gimmick. **A human should sign off on tone/timing/dignity before this publishes.** The pipeline picked him almost certainly because his death made him surge in search.

## What the piece argues
Type **4 (4w3, Sexual subtype)**, confidence high. Thesis: the absurd bowl-cut clown was how a hyper-self-conscious Individualist let himself be seen — an auteur who wrote, produced, mixed, and directed everything, made himself a meme so no one would catch him being sincere, and kept begging his audience to cry. The 4-vs-7 call is resolved in the Rabbit Hole (tiebreaker: he *built and inhabited* the outsider/hurt identity — companies named "Alien Boy," two grief albums — rather than fleeing it like a 7 would).

